1
00:00:15,410 --> 00:00:18,440
Mr. Term tried to rape Ms. Shen this afternoon.

2
00:00:20,977 --> 00:00:22,080
How did you get here?

3
00:00:22,237 --> 00:00:25,520
If he tries to do anything to you next time, I will protect you.

4
00:00:26,237 --> 00:00:27,680
It is not your job.

5
00:00:28,057 --> 00:00:30,720
And our bedroom is not your place either.

6
00:00:30,937 --> 00:00:32,860
I shouldn't have done anything that it wasn't place.

7
00:00:32,903 --> 00:00:35,340
But I really want you to know that

8
00:00:35,357 --> 00:00:36,962
I will be by your side forever.

9
00:00:37,503 --> 00:00:39,160
I am willing to do anything for you.

10
00:00:39,850 --> 00:00:41,280
I'd like to resign, sir.

11
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:43,050
You can't resign.

12
00:00:43,443 --> 00:00:45,000
I gave your family a lot of money,

13
00:00:45,490 --> 00:00:46,491
You are the right man for this job.

14
00:00:47,040 --> 00:00:49,080
It is not beyond your ability.

15
00:00:51,983 --> 00:00:53,720
If you really needed to suck up that bitch

16
00:00:53,884 --> 00:00:55,200
and you ignored my feelings like this,

17
00:00:55,480 --> 00:00:57,640
you should just divorce me and marry her instead.

18
00:00:58,043 --> 00:00:59,240
Get out of my face.

19
00:01:00,063 --> 00:01:02,600
He is not the same guy that I used to know.

20
00:01:02,817 --> 00:01:03,920
As a matter of fact,

21
00:01:04,217 --> 00:01:06,120
maybe I have never known him.

22
00:01:06,463 --> 00:01:08,200
Please don't change, Tone.

23
00:01:08,410 --> 00:01:09,411
Never,

24
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:11,700
I will never change.

25
00:01:14,263 --> 00:01:15,264
No way.

26
00:01:16,480 --> 00:01:19,760
I'm not going to divide your inheritance right now.

27
00:01:20,840 --> 00:01:22,880
It is as bad as you two cursing me to die.

28
00:01:24,423 --> 00:01:26,120
Who would do that to their own fathers?

29
00:01:26,690 --> 00:01:28,521
I asked you to divide the assets right now

30
00:01:28,703 --> 00:01:30,520
so Perm and I can use them for investment

31
00:01:30,903 --> 00:01:32,120
and their benefits will be flourished.

32
00:01:32,697 --> 00:01:35,760
It'd be a waste of time to gain it after your death.

33
00:01:35,920 --> 00:01:36,921
He's right.

34
00:01:37,743 --> 00:01:39,920
You know the situation quite well.

35
00:01:40,643 --> 00:01:43,600
They are trying to lay off government officers and urging us to do business.

36
00:01:44,720 --> 00:01:47,160
If we start it first, we will be richer first.

37
00:01:47,960 --> 00:01:49,360
Working as rip-off merchants?

38
00:01:50,440 --> 00:01:53,040
Our family has been nobility for ages,

39
00:01:53,763 --> 00:01:55,240
we have never been merchants

40
00:01:55,563 --> 00:01:58,960
and we have never begged people to buy our items.

41
00:01:59,650 --> 00:02:00,720
No way in hell!

42
00:02:01,083 --> 00:02:02,640
This is so outdated.

43
00:02:03,123 --> 00:02:05,224
My friend's families sold their vintage belongings and used them for funding.

44
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:06,281
Now they are getting rich.

45
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:08,040
And we have you, a rich guy who got stuck.

46
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:12,200
- Term! I am your father!
- Dad.

47
00:02:12,277 --> 00:02:13,480
He was right.

48
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:17,960
Your assets will pass on to us sooner or later.

49
00:02:20,043 --> 00:02:22,040
If you split them in half and give them to us,

50
00:02:22,770 --> 00:02:24,480
you will see us become wealthy before you die.

51
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:27,680
If you gave them to us when you passed away,

52
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:29,920
who would be proud of me?

53
00:02:30,230 --> 00:02:31,800
Shut your mouth right now!

54
00:02:33,337 --> 00:02:35,680
I know your true colors.

55
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:38,640
You two don't care about me.

56
00:02:39,640 --> 00:02:41,197
All you care about is my assets.

57
00:02:42,137 --> 00:02:43,440
If I am still alive,

58
00:02:44,357 --> 00:02:46,160
you two won't get any of that.

59
00:02:47,257 --> 00:02:48,700
If that is what you really think of us,

60
00:02:49,643 --> 00:02:50,720
please rush to the other side.

61
00:02:51,017 --> 00:02:53,760
Perm! Perm! You are so ungrateful!

62
00:02:54,110 --> 00:02:55,111
You!

63
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:07,321
Well, you're quite forebearing.

64
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:19,971
But I can wait.

65
00:05:44,283 --> 00:05:46,160
We've traveled so far from home

66
00:05:46,283 --> 00:05:47,880
we need to go home early.

67
00:05:49,637 --> 00:05:51,720
If we go home too late, they will get suspicious.

68
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:54,801
We can tell them that the car broke down.

69
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:57,360
And it takes time to fix it.

70
00:05:58,070 --> 00:06:00,040
It is a new car, how can it be broke down?

71
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:02,640
One more thing,

72
00:06:03,283 --> 00:06:04,480
I don't know how to fix a car.

73
00:06:05,543 --> 00:06:07,000
Or we can tell them

74
00:06:07,683 --> 00:06:09,040
that I make several stops to buy things.

75
00:06:11,783 --> 00:06:12,784
Where are they?

76
00:06:13,920 --> 00:06:14,921
Your items?

77
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,063
I don't care. When we get home,

78
00:06:20,150 --> 00:06:21,800
I will rush to my room.

79
00:06:21,943 --> 00:06:24,404
And I will leave you to answer all questions.

80
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:25,441
Oh my!

81
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:28,201
I can't lie to anyone.

82
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:31,700
If you wish me to lie, they will find out the truth.

83
00:06:33,077 --> 00:06:34,320
What should we tell them?

84
00:06:36,077 --> 00:06:37,357
I…

85
00:06:37,897 --> 00:06:39,320
will tell them that

86
00:06:41,880 --> 00:06:44,800
I take you to see a live Lakhon Chatri in the market.

87
00:06:46,077 --> 00:06:47,120
What do they perform?

88
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:50,901
Phra Aphai Mani,

89
00:06:53,057 --> 00:06:55,640
when he escaped the ogress and fell in love with the mermaid.

90
00:06:59,610 --> 00:07:02,720
Do the mermaid love Phra Aphai Mani back?

91
00:07:04,920 --> 00:07:05,921
Of course,

92
00:07:07,657 --> 00:07:08,658
very much.

93
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:15,601
And the mermaid took Phra Aphai Mani

94
00:07:16,050 --> 00:07:19,240
to the Koh Kaeo Phitsadan Island and be in love.

95
00:07:23,880 --> 00:07:26,480
You said you couldn't lie but that was quite a story.

96
00:07:26,703 --> 00:07:27,704
What?

97
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:31,681
What happened?

98
00:07:34,320 --> 00:07:36,160
You just called me a good liar.

99
00:07:37,880 --> 00:07:38,881
Are you not?

100
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:03,560
If I have to lie,

101
00:08:04,720 --> 00:08:06,480
I will only lie for you.

102
00:08:43,460 --> 00:08:44,720
Perm?

103
00:08:45,680 --> 00:08:47,481
Why are you home so early?

104
00:08:47,880 --> 00:08:49,200
They canceled the meeting for today.

105
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:52,320
Good, you should get some rest.

106
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,001
Come on, put these away.

107
00:09:45,480 --> 00:09:47,760
We are not fooling ourselves, are we?

108
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:49,640
Why did you ask me that?

109
00:09:54,210 --> 00:09:55,320
All my life,

110
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:58,360
I rarely meet with anything good.

111
00:10:00,663 --> 00:10:02,242
When I finally get to meet something good,

112
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:05,880
that thing won't stay with me for too long.

113
00:10:09,250 --> 00:10:10,960
I wish I had superpowers.

114
00:10:13,317 --> 00:10:14,960
I want to freeze this moment.

115
00:10:20,760 --> 00:10:21,761
It would be nice,

116
00:10:24,520 --> 00:10:27,160
if we could freeze our happy moments.

117
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:33,560
But we can't do that.

118
00:10:38,090 --> 00:10:40,310
We just need to do it like what my mom taught me.

119
00:10:47,870 --> 00:10:48,871
What did she teach you?

120
00:10:51,863 --> 00:10:53,040
When I was 10 years old,

121
00:10:54,077 --> 00:10:55,800
my mom was severely sick.

122
00:10:57,960 --> 00:10:59,000
The doctor said that

123
00:10:59,497 --> 00:11:01,560
she had less than one month to be with me.

124
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:06,720
I cried my heart out.

125
00:11:08,770 --> 00:11:10,050
She couldn't take it anymore

126
00:11:11,640 --> 00:11:12,721
and she said that she didn't die yet.

127
00:11:14,241 --> 00:11:15,242
She was still alive.

128
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:20,160
We should make every day count,

129
00:11:20,790 --> 00:11:22,080
create the most valuble memories,

130
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:26,640
until the day that we parted.

131
00:11:29,423 --> 00:11:30,520
After that,

132
00:11:32,320 --> 00:11:34,760
my mom and I were happy every day.

133
00:11:36,890 --> 00:11:38,320
We laughed

134
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:41,160
and smiled together

135
00:11:43,880 --> 00:11:45,250
until she was gone.

136
00:12:08,837 --> 00:12:10,600
I have no superpowers

137
00:12:11,730 --> 00:12:13,640
I can't freeze time.

138
00:12:18,857 --> 00:12:19,960
But I promise you that

139
00:12:21,880 --> 00:12:24,840
I will make you the happiest girl every day.

140
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:29,880
I will love you

141
00:12:32,503 --> 00:12:33,880
like you've always wanted to be loved.

142
00:12:41,170 --> 00:12:42,171
I love you.

143
00:12:45,637 --> 00:12:46,638
I love you.

144
00:13:35,877 --> 00:13:37,040
You said we needed to rush back.

145
00:13:49,203 --> 00:13:50,204
You're right.

146
00:14:29,197 --> 00:14:30,720
You're going out every day, Shen.

147
00:14:35,520 --> 00:14:36,777
It's because people

148
00:14:37,120 --> 00:14:38,720
keep on blaming me

149
00:14:39,040 --> 00:14:40,320
and sometimes

150
00:14:41,360 --> 00:14:42,480
they are trying to attack me.

151
00:14:43,080 --> 00:14:44,360
You should try to forget that.

152
00:14:45,040 --> 00:14:46,682
I didn't think it through and I was too aggressive.

153
00:14:47,520 --> 00:14:49,000
It's hard for me to forget.

154
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:52,201
So…

155
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:54,120
I saw you went out every day,

156
00:14:55,103 --> 00:14:56,104
where did you go?

157
00:14:59,203 --> 00:15:00,800
Why would you want to know?

158
00:15:01,757 --> 00:15:04,920
I could borrow the car and your driver

159
00:15:05,543 --> 00:15:06,880
to take my wife out and about.

160
00:15:08,250 --> 00:15:10,880
You need to ask your brother first,

161
00:15:11,651 --> 00:15:12,920
to see if he is okay with that.

162
00:15:15,283 --> 00:15:16,800
My brother is quite a generous man.

163
00:15:17,990 --> 00:15:20,200
He lets a good-looking driver to take care of his wife.

164
00:15:23,117 --> 00:15:24,440
Are you done talking?

165
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:26,960
I need to go upstairs to feed Khunphra.

166
00:16:14,271 --> 00:16:15,400
You work out a lot lately.

167
00:16:21,520 --> 00:16:22,521
Not so much, sir.

168
00:16:27,280 --> 00:16:28,281
Is something bothering you?

169
00:16:30,163 --> 00:16:31,320
Me? Nothing.

170
00:16:32,360 --> 00:16:33,837
What about you? Are you stressed out?

171
00:16:33,930 --> 00:16:35,120
That's why you box like crazy.

172
00:16:39,403 --> 00:16:40,404
No, sir.

173
00:16:41,520 --> 00:16:42,521
I just want to work out.

174
00:16:59,160 --> 00:17:01,120
Do you remember us boxing together when we were young?

175
00:17:04,937 --> 00:17:05,938
Yes, I do.

176
00:17:06,640 --> 00:17:07,920
Should we revive the memories?

177
00:18:47,790 --> 00:18:49,280
I won when we were young,

178
00:18:51,443 --> 00:18:52,700
and I won again this time.

179
00:19:06,623 --> 00:19:08,400
Tone, let me ask you something.

180
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:10,001
I saw that lately

181
00:19:10,480 --> 00:19:12,800
you went out with Ms. Shen and came home late every day.

182
00:19:13,480 --> 00:19:14,920
Where did you take her to?

183
00:19:15,750 --> 00:19:16,751
Why do you want to know?

184
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:18,640
Where she was going is none of your business.

185
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:20,440
But I want to know.

186
00:19:21,040 --> 00:19:22,640
It's her business, not yours.

187
00:19:24,570 --> 00:19:25,571
So what is it?

188
00:19:30,030 --> 00:19:31,031
Well, I…

189
00:19:31,203 --> 00:19:32,204
It depends.

190
00:19:32,440 --> 00:19:34,960
Sometimes she wanted to go shopping.

191
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:36,960
Sometimes she went to the market,

192
00:19:37,960 --> 00:19:39,961
or went back to her old house.

193
00:19:40,800 --> 00:19:42,150
- What about today?
- Come on.

194
00:19:42,470 --> 00:19:43,480
Stop asking questions already.

195
00:19:43,990 --> 00:19:45,320
I want to know.

196
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:48,241
Where did you go today? Tell me.

197
00:19:48,403 --> 00:19:49,200
I really want to know.

198
00:19:50,040 --> 00:19:51,280
To see a live Lakhon Chatri.

199
00:19:51,920 --> 00:19:52,921
What did they perform?

200
00:19:53,083 --> 00:19:56,084
See, you want to know it too?

201
00:19:57,200 --> 00:19:58,320
What was it?

202
00:20:01,640 --> 00:20:02,641
Phra Aphai Mani,

203
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:05,320
when he escaped the ogress and fell in love with the mermaid.

204
00:20:11,670 --> 00:20:14,840
I was wondering, how did human and mermaid do it?

205
00:20:15,583 --> 00:20:16,720
You pervert!

206
00:20:18,163 --> 00:20:21,080
What? I'm curious about this.

207
00:20:21,100 --> 00:20:22,400
Just eat it. Stop asking already.

208
00:20:22,440 --> 00:20:25,280
- So annoying.
- Stop talking already.

209
00:20:25,800 --> 00:20:26,801
Come on.

210
00:21:18,040 --> 00:21:19,700
The first night of our marriage,

211
00:21:20,763 --> 00:21:22,720
my husband taught me one English word.

212
00:21:24,164 --> 00:21:25,240
It is 'make love.'

213
00:21:27,543 --> 00:21:29,800
He said that it was the action to confirm

214
00:21:29,810 --> 00:21:31,320
that two people were really in love.

215
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:35,840
Since he came back from Penang,

216
00:21:37,110 --> 00:21:38,920
he has never confirmed the action to me.

217
00:21:46,323 --> 00:21:47,324
Well,

218
00:21:48,320 --> 00:21:51,040
let me teach you another English word.

219
00:21:55,777 --> 00:21:56,840
Eternal love.

220
00:21:59,240 --> 00:22:00,440
What does it mean?

221
00:22:01,762 --> 00:22:03,482
It means that I

222
00:22:04,810 --> 00:22:07,720
will love you forever.

223
00:22:17,090 --> 00:22:19,560
I've loved you since the first day that we met.

224
00:22:22,360 --> 00:22:23,600
And I promise you

225
00:22:24,361 --> 00:22:26,400
that I will love you forever.

226
00:22:34,750 --> 00:22:36,240
♪ There is real love ♪

227
00:22:37,243 --> 00:22:38,400
♪ existed ♪

228
00:22:39,200 --> 00:22:40,320
♪ in this world. ♪

229
00:22:42,730 --> 00:22:44,880
♪ I will hug you ♪

230
00:22:46,103 --> 00:22:47,920
♪ and I won't let you ♪

231
00:22:48,243 --> 00:22:50,680
♪ lose your faith.♪

232
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:55,200
♪ I promise that ♪

233
00:22:55,840 --> 00:22:57,220
♪ I will protect you ♪

234
00:22:58,000 --> 00:22:59,760
♪ forever. ♪

235
00:23:01,897 --> 00:23:03,760
♪ Because I was born ♪

236
00:23:04,737 --> 00:23:06,600
♪ to love you ♪

237
00:23:07,397 --> 00:23:08,960
♪ eternally. ♪

238
00:25:06,557 --> 00:25:07,558
I love you.

239
00:25:10,400 --> 00:25:11,401
I love you.

240
00:26:52,103 --> 00:26:53,700
Ms. Shen? What happened?

241
00:26:54,297 --> 00:26:56,440
I saw someone at the window, looking at us.

242
00:27:18,320 --> 00:27:19,490
I didn't see anyone.

243
00:27:20,703 --> 00:27:22,200
Are you sure about that?

244
00:27:25,600 --> 00:27:27,560
Of course, I'm sure.

245
00:27:29,097 --> 00:27:30,680
I think we should get dressed.

246
00:28:07,437 --> 00:28:09,438
Tone! Look!

247
00:28:17,017 --> 00:28:18,480
Are you sure these footprints aren't ours?

248
00:28:18,840 --> 00:28:21,040
I'm sure. I never stood here.

249
00:28:21,743 --> 00:28:24,000
- Did you stand here?
- No, I didn't.

250
00:28:25,880 --> 00:28:27,120
Who would it be?

251
00:28:27,962 --> 00:28:29,500
Do you think they will tell on us?

252
00:28:30,080 --> 00:28:31,240
I have no idea about this.

253
00:28:31,840 --> 00:28:33,400
I think we need to go.

254
00:29:10,490 --> 00:29:11,491
Juang.

255
00:29:11,997 --> 00:29:12,908
Yes, ma'am?

256
00:29:12,943 --> 00:29:13,944
Where did the mud come from?

257
00:29:14,600 --> 00:29:15,920
I have no idea, ma'am.

258
00:29:16,440 --> 00:29:18,441
I cleaned the upstairs with Chan all afternoon.

259
00:29:18,541 --> 00:29:19,880
I finished cleaning late

260
00:29:20,280 --> 00:29:22,881
and then I saw mud stains here.

261
00:29:26,977 --> 00:29:28,840
Is my husband home?

262
00:29:29,577 --> 00:29:30,578
He's here already.

263
00:29:30,650 --> 00:29:32,560
He was here at the same time as Mr. Term.

264
00:29:33,240 --> 00:29:34,680
Mr. Term just got home too?

265
00:29:35,040 --> 00:29:36,041
That's right.

266
00:29:38,080 --> 00:29:40,881
Did anyone leave the house this afternoon?

267
00:29:42,480 --> 00:29:43,920
I don't know, ma'am.

268
00:29:53,197 --> 00:29:54,250
- Chan?
- Yes, sir.

269
00:29:56,283 --> 00:29:58,720
When you're done with your work, clean my shoes.

270
00:29:59,120 --> 00:30:00,543
They are all muddy.

271
00:30:00,843 --> 00:30:01,844
Sure, sir.

272
00:30:07,360 --> 00:30:08,361
Why?

273
00:30:08,643 --> 00:30:10,700
Are you startled by seeing me?

274
00:30:11,840 --> 00:30:13,520
You just stood there and didn't make any noise.

275
00:30:13,837 --> 00:30:15,160
Anyone would get startled.

276
00:30:17,457 --> 00:30:20,040
Where are you going? You just got home.

277
00:30:22,063 --> 00:30:23,400
I forgot my things in the car.

278
00:30:57,743 --> 00:31:00,080
Did someone feed you today, Little Nualnoi?

279
00:31:07,937 --> 00:31:09,943
Tone, is it possible that

280
00:31:10,037 --> 00:31:11,880
my husband was the one who saw us?

281
00:31:12,480 --> 00:31:13,640
Why would you say that?

282
00:31:14,280 --> 00:31:16,400
He told Chan to clean his shoes,

283
00:31:16,543 --> 00:31:17,760
because they were muddy.

284
00:31:18,400 --> 00:31:20,840
Think about it, where in the ministry is full of mud?

285
00:31:20,970 --> 00:31:23,200
If it was really him, he wouldn't let it slide.

286
00:31:23,770 --> 00:31:25,401
He would have yelled at us on the spot.

287
00:31:25,800 --> 00:31:27,000
I don't think so.

288
00:31:28,280 --> 00:31:29,281
Who else could it be?

289
00:31:32,120 --> 00:31:33,156
Could it be Mr. Term?

290
00:31:33,840 --> 00:31:36,700
Since the incident, I saw him look at in weird way.

291
00:31:38,440 --> 00:31:39,441
You're right.

292
00:31:40,080 --> 00:31:41,440
Many days ago,

293
00:31:41,800 --> 00:31:43,252
he talked to me weirdly.

294
00:31:45,103 --> 00:31:47,400
What should we do? What if it was really him?

295
00:31:47,463 --> 00:31:48,880
He must have told on us for sure.

296
00:31:49,017 --> 00:31:50,200
Don't overthink about this, ma'am.

297
00:31:51,040 --> 00:31:52,920
I will go back to the cottage tomorrrow.

298
00:31:53,077 --> 00:31:54,640
Maybe we can find some evidence.

299
00:31:58,320 --> 00:32:00,560
It could be a villager in the area.

300
00:32:43,063 --> 00:32:44,064
Honey?

301
00:32:50,440 --> 00:32:51,441
That's all.

302
00:33:11,850 --> 00:33:13,570
What did Term need to talk to you about?

303
00:33:15,143 --> 00:33:17,100
Nothing much, just some government-related works.

304
00:33:18,800 --> 00:33:20,040
What works?

305
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:22,161
Why did you want to know?

306
00:33:22,961 --> 00:33:24,240
You don't know it even if I tell you.

307
00:33:27,970 --> 00:33:30,000
Is everything okay? You're acting weird.

308
00:33:32,743 --> 00:33:33,744
Nothing.

309
00:33:34,760 --> 00:33:37,320
I've never seen him talked to you in the office before.

310
00:33:40,120 --> 00:33:42,680
Let's have dinner. They're setting the table.

311
00:33:43,080 --> 00:33:45,800
Go ahead, I need to take care of some documents first.

312
00:34:10,085 --> 00:34:12,040
I'm here to warn you about Tone.

313
00:34:13,840 --> 00:34:15,600
I saw her leaving the house the him every day.

314
00:34:16,320 --> 00:34:17,320
I don't know where they went to.

315
00:34:18,137 --> 00:34:20,440
They're both young and it could lead to scandal.

316
00:34:21,003 --> 00:34:22,004
Why?

317
00:34:22,753 --> 00:34:23,754
Are you jealous for me?

318
00:34:24,682 --> 00:34:25,950
Why would I be?

319
00:34:27,010 --> 00:34:29,120
I just don't want them to fool you, that's all.

320
00:34:30,320 --> 00:34:31,720
I don't care if you would listen to me.

321
00:34:33,210 --> 00:34:34,400
Thank you for your concern.

322
00:34:35,040 --> 00:34:36,200
But don't worry.

323
00:34:37,080 --> 00:34:40,060
If anything happens, I will take care of it.

324
00:34:43,520 --> 00:34:45,640
- Suit yourself.
- Honey?

325
00:34:52,200 --> 00:34:53,201
That's all.

326
00:35:36,190 --> 00:35:37,480
Why are you looking at her?

327
00:35:40,800 --> 00:35:43,801
I'm observing her because she looks livelier than before.

328
00:35:47,190 --> 00:35:48,480
You must take a good care of her.

329
00:35:50,000 --> 00:35:52,001
Don't focus on his wife,

330
00:35:52,443 --> 00:35:53,840
focus on your wife.

331
00:35:54,417 --> 00:35:56,600
Rayrai seems more depressed than yesterday.

332
00:36:00,217 --> 00:36:02,400
I'm about to ask for Perm's tips to cheer her up.

333
00:36:03,520 --> 00:36:04,521
Or…

334
00:36:05,557 --> 00:36:07,200
I should spoil my wife with a car

335
00:36:08,200 --> 00:36:09,201
and a driver.

336
00:36:10,720 --> 00:36:13,700
Perhaps Rayrai could be lively like Shen.

337
00:36:14,880 --> 00:36:15,881
No need to.

338
00:36:16,563 --> 00:36:18,560
I am not demanding that much.

339
00:36:19,403 --> 00:36:21,960
I'm happy just to see you take care of my basic needs.

340
00:36:32,697 --> 00:36:34,840
I'm taking a good care of you now, happy?

341
00:36:36,010 --> 00:36:37,480
If you don't mean it, don't force it.

342
00:36:37,550 --> 00:36:39,000
Who said that I didn't mean it?

343
00:36:39,083 --> 00:36:40,360
Oh, come on!

344
00:36:41,017 --> 00:36:43,360
I've told you for so many times not to fight during dinner.

345
00:36:46,160 --> 00:36:47,240
It's because of you again.

346
00:36:48,057 --> 00:36:50,560
You did nothing, still they were in fight because of you.

347
00:36:51,200 --> 00:36:52,400
You are unbelievable.

348
00:36:53,920 --> 00:36:55,760
- Is it my fault?
- That's enough.

349
00:36:58,000 --> 00:36:59,120
Stop fighting already.

350
00:37:03,177 --> 00:37:04,760
I've told you that talking back to her is pointless.

351
00:37:11,603 --> 00:37:12,960
Where exactly did you go today?

352
00:37:18,857 --> 00:37:20,640
I went back to my house to see my dad.

353
00:37:21,437 --> 00:37:22,438
You did?

354
00:37:23,480 --> 00:37:24,881
Why did your nanny, Lang,

355
00:37:25,923 --> 00:37:27,400
came to see you this afternoon?

356
00:37:27,637 --> 00:37:29,400
She brought back your stuff.

357
00:37:33,057 --> 00:37:34,058
Yes, ma'am.

358
00:37:48,880 --> 00:37:51,200
She told me that you left a skirt for her to alter.

359
00:37:51,800 --> 00:37:54,280
She finished it a whiel ago but you never went back home.

360
00:37:59,080 --> 00:38:01,520
Where did you go today?

361
00:38:04,960 --> 00:38:06,120
We missed each other.

362
00:38:07,400 --> 00:38:10,440
I went for a walk at Phra Sumen Fort first,

363
00:38:10,643 --> 00:38:12,441
then I stopped by my house in late afternoon.

364
00:38:13,230 --> 00:38:15,080
I didn't catch Lang when I was there either.

365
00:38:16,120 --> 00:38:17,720
They also told me that

366
00:38:17,830 --> 00:38:19,360
Lang left my skirt here already.

367
00:38:20,783 --> 00:38:21,784
Thank you.

368
00:38:24,480 --> 00:38:26,160
I really appreciate you

369
00:38:26,443 --> 00:38:27,760
receiving the skirt for me.

370
00:38:35,050 --> 00:38:37,040
You go out every day like this.

371
00:38:37,950 --> 00:38:38,951
I know that

372
00:38:39,120 --> 00:38:41,880
Perm allows you to go anywhere you want.

373
00:38:43,320 --> 00:38:44,920
But you should talk about this with your wife.

374
00:39:04,157 --> 00:39:07,040
I brought sweet longan for everyone.

375
00:39:07,143 --> 00:39:08,600
Come here, now.

376
00:39:08,644 --> 00:39:11,045
Khunying told me to go to the market this afternoon

377
00:39:11,100 --> 00:39:12,920
and wanted me to share with everyone.

378
00:39:13,101 --> 00:39:15,560
- Let me try some.
- Tone, do you want it?

379
00:39:16,080 --> 00:39:17,800
No, thanks. I don't want to get a mouth ulcer.

380
00:39:18,537 --> 00:39:19,960
It's better than catching something else.

381
00:39:22,560 --> 00:39:23,640
What do you mean by that?

382
00:39:25,397 --> 00:39:28,500
Nothing. I was just joking with you.

383
00:39:31,143 --> 00:39:33,840
Shin, come here. Let me ask you something.

384
00:39:34,480 --> 00:39:36,960
I want to know about the new bike that Khunying bought for you.

385
00:39:37,123 --> 00:39:38,360
How was it?

386
00:39:38,643 --> 00:39:40,960
I really like it, it's fun to ride.

387
00:39:41,017 --> 00:39:43,200
I rode it around the city today.

388
00:39:44,363 --> 00:39:45,800
That's why you came home so late.

389
00:39:45,893 --> 00:39:46,894
Hmmm.

390
00:39:47,647 --> 00:39:49,400
What do you mean by that?

391
00:39:49,800 --> 00:39:51,520
I'm making noice to Khunying's favorite servant.

392
00:39:51,760 --> 00:39:54,800
Your old bike was broken just a little,

393
00:39:54,977 --> 00:39:56,997
and you asked her for a new one already.

394
00:39:58,700 --> 00:40:01,000
- Jealous much?
- So much.

395
00:40:19,090 --> 00:40:20,400
Are you alright?

396
00:40:24,323 --> 00:40:25,324
You care about me?

397
00:41:28,630 --> 00:41:29,631
Mr. Perm.

398
00:41:38,290 --> 00:41:39,720
Do you have anything to tell me?

399
00:41:47,630 --> 00:41:50,200
What do you mean by that?

400
00:41:52,970 --> 00:41:54,560
I just want to know where you took her today.

401
00:41:55,863 --> 00:41:57,320
Did she look happy?

402
00:41:59,310 --> 00:42:00,560
She looked happy, sir.

403
00:42:01,943 --> 00:42:04,160
She just wanted to ride around the city

404
00:42:05,190 --> 00:42:06,880
and walked around Bang Lamphu.

405
00:42:08,560 --> 00:42:10,000
Not Phra Sumen Fort?

406
00:42:14,440 --> 00:42:15,541
She went to Bang Lamphu first,

407
00:42:16,320 --> 00:42:17,721
then she visited Phra Sumen Fort after.

408
00:42:21,977 --> 00:42:23,560
Did you visit her house?

409
00:42:27,810 --> 00:42:28,811
Yes, we did.

410
00:42:29,663 --> 00:42:30,664
Late afternoon, sir.

411
00:42:33,790 --> 00:42:34,791
Good.

412
00:42:35,301 --> 00:42:36,520
Take a good care of her.

413
00:42:37,370 --> 00:42:38,371
Yes, sir.

414
00:43:21,770 --> 00:43:22,771
Tone!

415
00:43:23,610 --> 00:43:24,611
Shin!

416
00:43:24,903 --> 00:43:28,040
Why did you look so grumpy?

417
00:43:29,200 --> 00:43:30,201
What's on your mind?

418
00:43:31,240 --> 00:43:32,400
Do you need to know everything?

419
00:43:33,103 --> 00:43:35,360
Sure, I do.

420
00:43:36,960 --> 00:43:38,320
And I know something.

421
00:43:40,810 --> 00:43:41,811
What did you know?

422
00:43:46,640 --> 00:43:48,160
About you and Ms. Shen

423
00:43:48,643 --> 00:43:50,080
and what happened in the cottage by the rice field.

424
00:43:59,723 --> 00:44:00,724
It was you?

425
00:44:01,897 --> 00:44:03,680
Yup, it was me.

426
00:44:06,480 --> 00:44:08,881
Khunying told me to go to the market this afternoon

427
00:44:09,440 --> 00:44:12,280
on the way back, I wanted to enjoy my ride a little longer.

428
00:44:12,720 --> 00:44:14,300
So I took a longer route

429
00:44:15,640 --> 00:44:17,560
then I rode pass the cottage

430
00:44:20,680 --> 00:44:22,320
and I saw your car.

431
00:44:39,550 --> 00:44:41,100
So I stopped by.

432
00:45:02,537 --> 00:45:03,680
And I saw you two.

433
00:45:24,157 --> 00:45:27,040
I'm sorry for interrupting you.

434
00:45:27,243 --> 00:45:29,520
It seemed like you were having fun.

435
00:45:29,590 --> 00:45:30,591
Shin!

436
00:45:31,520 --> 00:45:32,800
You can't tell anyone about it.

437
00:45:33,200 --> 00:45:34,520
Oh, come on!

438
00:45:35,357 --> 00:45:36,560
It's your happiness.

439
00:45:36,960 --> 00:45:38,440
Of course, I won't tell anyone.

440
00:45:38,610 --> 00:45:40,000
It's not like that.

441
00:45:40,611 --> 00:45:42,560
What was it like then?

442
00:45:44,640 --> 00:45:45,641
Come on.

443
00:45:47,680 --> 00:45:49,040
Let's just say that

444
00:45:50,320 --> 00:45:52,160
I will try to keep it to myself for as long as I can.

445
00:45:54,520 --> 00:45:55,560
But you know me well.

446
00:45:56,421 --> 00:45:58,080
I tend to be talkative.

447
00:45:59,417 --> 00:46:01,400
And I'm worried that

448
00:46:01,880 --> 00:46:05,280
one day I could talk about it unintentionally.

449
00:46:07,960 --> 00:46:08,961
Shin!

450
00:46:10,240 --> 00:46:11,560
What do you mean by that?

451
00:46:12,800 --> 00:46:13,801
Just tell me!

452
00:46:14,401 --> 00:46:15,720
I'm done with your cryptic message.

453
00:46:16,360 --> 00:46:17,761
I need something to keep my mouth shut.

454
00:46:19,757 --> 00:46:20,758
Shin!

455
00:46:21,097 --> 00:46:22,720
- You're such…
- Stop, right there!

456
00:46:23,043 --> 00:46:24,160
Don't scold me.

457
00:46:24,920 --> 00:46:26,520
You know that I'm a sensitive person.

458
00:46:33,890 --> 00:46:34,891
How much money do you want?

459
00:46:36,037 --> 00:46:37,038
Tell me.

460
00:46:37,737 --> 00:46:38,738
Tone!

461
00:46:39,870 --> 00:46:41,160
I don't want any money.

462
00:46:44,040 --> 00:46:46,120
When I sneaked up on both of you,

463
00:46:49,283 --> 00:46:51,000
I couldn't help but think

464
00:46:51,740 --> 00:46:53,360
how wonderful this feeling would be.

465
00:46:56,450 --> 00:46:58,560
- I want the same feeling.
- Shin!

466
00:46:58,823 --> 00:47:00,720
Don't you dare think of Ms. Shen in a dirty way!

467
00:47:02,400 --> 00:47:04,040
I'm not aiming that high.

468
00:47:05,801 --> 00:47:07,200
It's not Ms. Shen that I am talking about.

469
00:47:16,083 --> 00:47:17,160
I was thinking of doing it with you.

470
00:47:20,790 --> 00:47:22,600
I want you to do that with me too.

471
00:48:08,080 --> 00:48:09,081
What do you say, Tone?

472
00:48:12,050 --> 00:48:13,200
The easiest way to shut me up.

473
00:48:14,817 --> 00:48:15,818
One time.

474
00:48:17,677 --> 00:48:18,678
Maybe…

475
00:48:20,000 --> 00:48:21,520
you would like it.

476
00:48:21,623 --> 00:48:22,624
Shin!

477
00:48:22,720 --> 00:48:24,680
- We could get struck by lightning.
- I don't care.

478
00:48:26,010 --> 00:48:27,600
Hit me hard, I like it.

479
00:48:28,920 --> 00:48:30,100
Is this a joke?

480
00:48:30,800 --> 00:48:31,880
It's not a joke.

481
00:48:41,243 --> 00:48:42,244
Tone,

482
00:48:44,244 --> 00:48:46,520
you know it well that my mouth can't be trusted.

483
00:48:48,245 --> 00:48:50,320
If you want to shut it,

484
00:48:52,080 --> 00:48:53,120
first things first,

485
00:48:54,960 --> 00:48:57,100
- you need to shut it with yours.
- Shin!

486
00:48:58,450 --> 00:49:00,560
Goddamnit!

487
00:49:00,880 --> 00:49:02,700
I needed your lips, not your punch.

488
00:49:03,600 --> 00:49:05,800
Oh, calm down.

489
00:49:06,640 --> 00:49:07,920
I understand that this is your first time.

490
00:49:08,720 --> 00:49:10,160
And you need to process.

491
00:49:18,570 --> 00:49:19,571
Let's just say that

492
00:49:20,917 --> 00:49:22,320
I will give you one night to prepare.

493
00:49:24,683 --> 00:49:25,760
Tomorrow night,

494
00:49:27,910 --> 00:49:29,000
you will do it with me

495
00:49:29,880 --> 00:49:30,960
the same as you did it with Ms. Shen.

496
00:49:32,883 --> 00:49:33,884
Otherwise,

497
00:49:35,120 --> 00:49:36,160
I could slip

498
00:49:37,000 --> 00:49:39,640
and tell everyone in this house.

499
00:50:19,197 --> 00:50:20,198
Tone.

500
00:50:40,888 --> 00:50:43,120
Did you get more clues

501
00:50:43,130 --> 00:50:44,200
about who watched us yesterday?

502
00:50:44,720 --> 00:50:46,720
- I think I know.
- Who are they?

503
00:50:47,320 --> 00:50:48,600
They are not from this house.

504
00:50:49,240 --> 00:50:51,500
Just a random crazy person.

505
00:50:52,160 --> 00:50:53,440
How did you know?

506
00:50:54,223 --> 00:50:56,000
I looked under the house this morning.

507
00:50:56,440 --> 00:50:58,240
And I saw a rag doll.

508
00:50:59,200 --> 00:51:01,160
I asked the villagers about the owner.

509
00:51:01,920 --> 00:51:03,120
They said that it belonged to a crazy person.

510
00:51:06,003 --> 00:51:07,280
I can't get anything out of that person.

511
00:51:09,042 --> 00:51:10,880
Even if they told on us,

512
00:51:11,400 --> 00:51:12,640
nobody would care.

513
00:51:15,960 --> 00:51:17,200
That's a relief.

514
00:51:19,923 --> 00:51:22,680
Why did you still look so worried about it?

515
00:51:24,044 --> 00:51:25,600
I was just tired.

516
00:51:26,700 --> 00:51:27,701
Are you sick?

517
00:51:31,237 --> 00:51:32,238
No, ma'am.

518
00:51:33,320 --> 00:51:34,880
I didn't sleep well last night

519
00:51:36,321 --> 00:51:37,400
because I was worried about this.

520
00:51:38,543 --> 00:51:40,200
I went out to search for more clues this morning.

521
00:51:42,000 --> 00:51:43,160
You should get some rest.

522
00:51:44,440 --> 00:51:45,441
Yes, ma'am.

523
00:52:08,323 --> 00:52:10,680
There is nothing interested in the news?

524
00:52:11,117 --> 00:52:12,240
You keep on flipping it.

525
00:52:13,080 --> 00:52:15,100
Just a moment, ma'am. I'm searching for one.

526
00:52:24,000 --> 00:52:25,360
It's about people having an affair.

527
00:52:27,001 --> 00:52:29,560
With who? Read it for me.

528
00:52:31,640 --> 00:52:35,160
Thorn is having an affair with Saeng.

529
00:52:35,920 --> 00:52:38,800
They were secret lovers

530
00:52:39,320 --> 00:52:42,520
while Saeng's husband went out of town to work

531
00:52:43,000 --> 00:52:44,720
for three months.

532
00:52:45,157 --> 00:52:46,560
Oh my goodness!

533
00:52:47,080 --> 00:52:49,881
People's morals keep going lower and lower.

534
00:52:50,320 --> 00:52:52,360
They don't know how to control themselves anymore.

535
00:52:53,083 --> 00:52:54,084
You're right.

536
00:52:54,960 --> 00:52:56,080
This type of scandal

537
00:52:56,343 --> 00:52:58,480
often happens right around us.

538
00:52:59,520 --> 00:53:00,521
Around us?

539
00:53:01,240 --> 00:53:02,360
Who are you talking about?

540
00:53:04,920 --> 00:53:06,680
You know someone who is having an affair?

541
00:53:10,003 --> 00:53:11,400
Well…

542
00:53:14,004 --> 00:53:15,720
When I went to buy longan yesterday,

543
00:53:16,880 --> 00:53:18,800
I saw….

544
00:53:22,437 --> 00:53:23,920
sellers chatting in the market

545
00:53:24,360 --> 00:53:27,280
that a wife living in a house across the market had an affair.

546
00:53:27,490 --> 00:53:30,160
But I didn't ask for details

547
00:53:30,191 --> 00:53:31,192
which house it is.

548
00:54:04,230 --> 00:54:05,600
I've told you that

549
00:54:09,240 --> 00:54:11,100
I can do anything for you.

550
00:54:40,903 --> 00:54:41,904
Hey!

551
00:54:43,103 --> 00:54:44,104
Let's get it over with.

552
00:54:51,610 --> 00:54:52,611
That's more like it.

553
00:55:35,840 --> 00:55:37,240
You followed my order well.

554
00:55:40,777 --> 00:55:41,778
Your secret

555
00:55:42,320 --> 00:55:43,840
is safe with me for sure.

556
00:56:17,520 --> 00:56:19,400
I will help you out, so you can do it easier.

557
00:56:56,063 --> 00:56:57,920
- Shin!
- What is wrong with you?

558
00:56:58,560 --> 00:56:59,880
You should take a shower first.

559
00:57:05,523 --> 00:57:06,524
Fine.

560
00:57:09,320 --> 00:57:10,321
But you…

561
00:57:14,997 --> 00:57:16,880
need to stay where you are.

562
00:58:27,750 --> 00:58:28,880
Where is Shin?

563
00:58:35,600 --> 00:58:36,960
We should end this.

564
00:58:37,880 --> 00:58:38,881
Why is that?

565
00:58:39,763 --> 00:58:41,730
We should go back to be just a boss

566
00:58:43,164 --> 00:58:45,360
and a driver as it should be.

567
00:58:49,030 --> 00:58:50,520
Who are you talking to?

568
00:58:52,840 --> 00:58:53,844
Ms. Shen.
